Description: This guitar hits WAY above it's weight class. AWESOME looking and playing relic'd 1994-1995 MIM stratocaster. purchased from an ebay seller with over 30 years of experience building and restoring guitars. 1961 features and 100% Fender Parts (except for the upgraded Hand Wound Alnico Pickups). C Profile Neck, 9.5" radius, brand new Fender 5 way switch, full sized pots, rounded (rolled) edges of fretboard with vintage tuners and decal. Nitrocellulose primer/colorcoat/clear coat. Fender Mint green pick guard and backplate. I upgraded the MIM pickups to a set of Fat PupsVintage Mongrel 5/2 Hand Wound Alnico pickups sold by ebay seller fatpups (please look him u and read more about these awesome pickups and read through his sellers feedback!). The bridge pickup has a brass bridge plate. These pickups sound incredible and offer vintage tone and a bridge pickup without the typical shrill that cheaper pickups have. This guitar has a great "feel", and the neck is very comfortable to play with a nice sanded back. Setup is nice and fast and frets look great with little to no wear. What you have here is the experience of a Fender custom shop guitar at a fraction of the price. Just a great guitar that's sure to please. Comes with a used vinyl gig bag. Please feel free to ask questions. Item will be packaged very well to ensure safe delivery.
Title: Fender Stratocaster Relic Shell Pink Electric Guitar
